For the time being, see the section in the main INSTALL file about
installing the OCaml GODI distribution.

For editing, [Taureg-mode][tm] is recommended over the default ocaml
emacs mode.  As an example, you can add the following lines to your
`.emacs` file to enable it:

;; tuareg-mode 1.45.6
(add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs-modes/tuareg-mode-1.45.6")
(setq auto-mode-alist (cons '("\\.ml\\w?" . tuareg-mode) auto-mode-alist))
(autoload 'tuareg-mode "tuareg" "Major mode for editing Caml code" t)
(autoload 'camldebug "camldebug" "Run the Caml debugger" t)
(add-hook 'tuareg-mode-hook 'toggle-input-method)

Make sure to edit the path string to the location where you actually
put tuareg-mode on your computer.

[tm]: http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~acohen/tuareg/